<body>
    <h1>Using Kube Hunter for kubernetes testing</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>Running a kube-hunter test on your cluster will show you what th=
e attackers are seeing and how to fix the problem. </p>
<h2 id=3D"UsingKubeHunterforkubernetestesting-Kube-hunterScanningoptions"><=
strong>Kube-hunter Scanning options</strong></h2>
<p>There are three scanning options to run kube-hunter:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Remote scanning (scans one or more specific IPs or DNS names)</p></l=
i>
<li><p>Interface scanning (scans subnets on all local network interfaces)</=
p></li>
<li><p>IP range scanning (scans a given IP range)</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"UsingKubeHunterforkubernetestesting-Runningkube-hunterasacontaine=
r"><strong>Running kube-hunter as a container</strong></h2>
<p>Aqua Security maintains a containerized version of kube-hunter at <code>=
aquasec/kube-hunter</code>.</p>
<p>We could either run:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Run container with reporting plugin for uploading results into a rep=
ort that can be viewed at <a href=3D"https://kube-hunter.aquasec.com" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">kube-hunter.aquasec.com</a>.</p></li>
<li><p>Run container without the reporting plugin</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"UsingKubeHunterforkubernetestesting-Stepstorunkube-hunterasaconta=
iner(withoutreportingplugin)">Steps to run kube-hunter as a container (with=
out reporting plugin)</h3>
<p>The steps to set up kube-hunter are as follows:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Connect to the server.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcloud =
compute ssh dev-k8-master-01</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Run kube-hunter container with the host network, it will be able to =
probe all the interfaces on the host:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">docker =
run -it --rm --network host aquasec/kube-hunter</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Choose a scanning options: Lets say we choose option 1:</p></li>
</ol>
<div id=3D"expander-581044844" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-581044844" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"976345cb5c45a9cd04afeb0463f22a9d" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Choose on=
e of the options below:</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-581044844" class=3D"expand-content">
<ol>
<li><p>Remote scanning (scans one or more specific IPs or DNS names)</p></l=
i>
<li><p>Interface scanning (scans subnets on all local network interfaces)</=
p></li>
<li><p>IP range scanning (scans a given IP range)</p></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<p>4. Then we need to enter the private IP address of the server. This can =
be retrieved with the below command</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">hostnam=
e -I|awk '{print $1}'</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>5. Scan result displays on the terminal</p>
<h3 id=3D"UsingKubeHunterforkubernetestesting-Stepstorunkube-hunterasaconta=
iner(withreportingplugin)">Steps to run kube-hunter as a container (with re=
porting plugin)</h3>
<p>The steps to set up kube-hunter are as follows:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Connect to the server.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcloud =
compute ssh dev-k8-master-01</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>At the <a href=3D"https://kube-hunter.aquasec.com" class=3D"external=
-link" rel=3D"nofollow">kube-hunter site</a>, enter your email address and =
you=E2=80=99ll get a Docker command to run that <strong>includes a token.</=
strong></p></li>
<li><p>Copy that command and run it on your node. You=E2=80=99ll be prompte=
d for the address of the cluster to test against.</p></li>
<li><p>Run kube-hunter container with the host network, it will be able to =
probe all the interfaces on the host:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">docker =
run -it --rm --network host aquasec/kube-hunter '&lt;&lt;secret token&gt;&g=
t;'</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Choose a scanning options:</p></li>
</ol>
