<h2 id=3D"UsingKubeHunterforkubernetestesting-Runkube-hunterasajob">Run kub=
e-hunter as a job</h2>
<p>The steps to set up kube-hunter are as follows:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Connect to the bastion server.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcloud =
compute ssh dev-dr-bastion</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Clone the repository:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git clo=
ne https://github.com/aquasecurity/kube-hunter.git</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Run the kube-hunter pod in your cluster:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">kubectl=
 create -f kube-hunter/job.yaml</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p>nacho@dev-dr-bastion:~/tools$ kubectl apply -f kube-hunter/job.yam=
l<br>job.batch/kube-hunter created</p></li>
<li><p>Wait for the job and the corresponding pods to be completed.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">kubectl=
 get jobs,pods</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
</ol>
<div id=3D"expander-848653676" class=3D"expand-container">
